&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; Follow-up on Spec-Driven Development Two Months Later: spec-kit and Ecosystem Development Research
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &amp;lt;/h3&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &amp;lt;p &lt;span class="nv"&gt;style&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;margin:0 0 10px; color:#555; font-size:14px; line-height:1.4;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; This article follows up on the rapid development of GitHub&lt;span class="s1"&gt;&amp;#39;s spec-kit project two months after its release, including its community growth, feature iterations, and ecosystem status. It also explores the core concepts of Specification Driven Development (SDD), compares main tools, discusses challenges, and outlines industry trends for 2025, providing developers with practical advice and outlook.
